eu.fbk.dkm.internal.springles.config

Class SpringlesRepositoryFactory.Config

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.fbk.dkm.internal.springles.config.SpringlesRepositoryFactory.Config
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.openrdf.repository.config.RepositoryImplConfig
    Enclosing class:
    SpringlesRepositoryFactory

    private static final class SpringlesRepositoryFactory.Config
extends Object
implements org.openrdf.repository.config.RepositoryImplConfig
    Helper class storing configuration data and adhering to the RepositoryImplConfig Sesame API.

    Instances of this class are just wrappers that store the supplied RDF configuration data (the part related to the repository implementation) so that it can be used when delegating creation and validation to the Factory mechanism.

      • parse

        public void parse(org.openrdf.model.Graph graph,
         org.openrdf.model.Resource implNode)
        Extracts the RDF triples describing the repository implementation and the resources that are transitively linked (as triple objects) to that implementation. This selection of RDF data is mandatory in order to avoid importing statements about other nodes, particularly the Sesame rep:Repository node (which is related to ID and title metadata about the repository and is distinct from the repository implementation node managed in this class). If information about that node is imported, then it will be also exported as part of the execution of export(Graph), causing Sesame to store duplicate data in its system repository, which would then become partly unusable. This method also reuses the Sesame repository ID as the ID assigned through property SPC.HAS_ID to the repository implementation, if missing.
        Specified by:
        parse in interface org.openrdf.repository.config.RepositoryImplConfig
